# INGetCarPowerLevelStatusIntentResponseObserver

**Protocol**

The interface for providing updates of a vehicle’s power level.

## Declaration

```swift
protocol INGetCarPowerLevelStatusIntentResponseObserver : NSObjectProtocol
```

## Overview

This protocol allows adopting objects to provide the system with an updated power level of a vehicle. You do not adopt this protocol in your own objects. Instead, the system provides an object that adopts this protocol, and you call its [doc://com.apple.sirikit/documentation/Intents/INGetCarPowerLevelStatusIntentResponseObserver/didUpdate(getCarPowerLevelStatus:)] method to provide the vehicle’s current power level.

When the system requests power level updates, it passes an object that conforms to this protocol to the [doc://com.apple.sirikit/documentation/Intents/INGetCarPowerLevelStatusIntentHandling/startSendingUpdates(for:to:)] method of your power level status handler—your custom object that adopts the [doc://com.apple.sirikit/documentation/Intents/INGetCarPowerLevelStatusIntentHandling] protocol. Your handler must store a reference to this object and use it to deliver regular updates about the power level.

## Updating the Power Level Status

- **didUpdate(getCarPowerLevelStatus:)**: Provides information about the vehicle’s power level.

## Get Car Power Level Status

- **INGetCarPowerLevelStatusIntentHandling**: The handler interface for requesting a car’s current power level.
- **INGetCarPowerLevelStatusIntent**: A request for the current power level of the user’s car.
- **INGetCarPowerLevelStatusIntentResponse**: Your app’s response to a request for the vehicle power level.
